Gabru-Agent
===========

Gabru-Agent — Generative Agent for Build, Review & Unit-test.

This project is a substantially modified derivative of Hermes Agent,
an open-source AI agent framework developed by Nous Research.

Upstream project
----------------
  Name:       Hermes Agent
  Homepage:   https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent
  Copyright:  Copyright (c) 2025 Nous Research
  License:    MIT License (see LICENSE)

The MIT license terms of the upstream project are preserved in the LICENSE
file at the root of this repository. Per those terms, the Hermes Agent
copyright notice and permission notice are retained.

Gabru-Agent has been significantly restructured for the Smart AI 2.0
Autonomous Dev track. Large portions of the upstream codebase —
including messaging-platform gateways, multi-provider adapters,
RL-training infrastructure, the TypeScript TUI, and most bundled skills —
have been removed. Remaining modules have been renamed, re-scoped, and
refactored to serve a specialized multi-agent (Coder / Tester / Vuln-Hunter)
software-engineering pipeline.
